<TEXT>
american telephone amp telegraph co wants to 
make it easier for americans to reach out and touch someone in the 
soviet union 
atampt said wednesday that if the federal communications 
commission approves it will start routing operatorassisted 
direct dialed data and video services onto the soviet intersputnik 
satellite system for the first time 
atampt currently has the only western phone facilities to the 
soviet union with other long distance companies leasing space on 
atampt lines the traffic is carried on 32 circuits by undersea cable 
and land lines as well as the intelsat satellite consortium 
despite these links which since last month has included atampt 
direct dial service to moscow demand still far exceeds existing 
capacity the phone company said 
atampt plans to add 24 more circuits in january and the 
proposal we made today could add as many as 150 additional 
circuits atampt spokesman herb linnen said 
the plan would require construction of a new 1 million antenna 
at atampts roaring creek earth station near catawissa pa linnen 
said 
it would take six months to construct the antenna which then 
would be aimed at an intersputnik satellite located in a 
geostationary orbit 22300 miles above a point just off the coast 
of liberia 
intersputnik is a consortium of 15 socialist countries that 
provides satellitedelivered communications among its member 
nations currently cable news network uses intersputnik for 
satellite news feeds linnen noted 
in a letter to president bush announcing its new plan atampt 
chairman robert allen said expanded communications capacity will 
result in direct economic benefits to the united states as we 
expand world trade through commercial relationships with eastern 
europe 
linnen said presidential approval was not needed for the plan 
which he said did not involve any national security issues such as 
transferring hightech equipment to communist nations 
he said the plan which was negotiated over the past 12 months 
was forwarded to bush as a matter of courtesy given bushs 
statements since the malta summit on improving ussoviet 
relations 
an atamptintersputnik link would be a blow to intelsat the 
117nation satellite cooperative that handles the bulk of 
international telephone traffic intelsat recently launched the 
first of a series of five new satellites it plans to put aloft over 
the next two years to handle increasing international 
communications traffic 
atampt said the soviets prefer using their own satellites for 
additional circuits because moscow then incurs expenses solely 
within the soviet union payable in rubles rather than in western 
currencies rubles are not traded officially in international money 
markets 
intelsat officials would not comment wednesday 
under the proposal atampt and the soviets would continue to use 
intelsat for some circuits and would split future increases in 
demand for circuits among undersea cables intelsat satellites and 
intersputnik satellites 
</TEXT>
