1988 
the state parole board voted 61 for parole after a 15minute 
hearing in which she pleaded i just ask for forgiveness i just 
want you to know i have changed my way of thinking 
mrs smith 38 who earned a high school diploma overcame drug 
and alcohol abuse remarried and began a successful career in real 
estate during her decade at large is to be released friday from 
the womens correctional center in columbia 
im sure its going to be hard to stay in a little cell 
knowing freedom is imminent mrs smith said at a news conference 
after the boards vote 
asked what she would do in her final hours behind bars mrs 
smith replied i think that i can do a lot of reflecting back 
over that time and just feel very thankful its not much 
longer 
the board rejected mrs smiths request for a pardon in may 
under parole conditions set by the board she will be under 
supervision by maryland authorities until march 1996 she also must 
make restitution to a jewlery store that she robbed of 4300 in 
cash and jewelry in 1974 
in january 1978 mrs smith then known as pamela rodgers 
walked away from a workrelease center in columbia while serving a 
12year sentence for armed robbery 
she changed her name married and became a real estate agent 
but in may 1988 maryland police acting on a tip from her 
exhusband daniel rodgers arrested mrs smith at her new home in 
severn md 
her second husband ray smith and her sons daniel rodgers 19 
and james rodgers 18 had been unaware of her past life 
after her recapture south carolina allowed mrs smith to serve 
her time at a prison in jessup md so she could be near her 
family she was brought to columbia this week for the parole 
hearing 
because of her conviction mrs smith may not be able to obtain 
a business license in maryland to resume her real estate career 
she said she plans to recruit and train real estate agents and try 
to lead a normal life without fear of the law 
i hope to just be settled and have a routine day with a 
routine job and a routine home life she said 
mrs smith expressed remorse over her past saying i wish 
that i could take it all back but i cant 
she also said she had matured as a result of her recapture and 
incarceration 
ive learned to work out my problems step by step and be 
rational mrs smith said most of all i take responsibility 
for my own direction and life pamela rodgers was not quite there 
at all 
ew pace owner of a greenville jewelry store robbed by mrs 
smith said he wants her to return the money stolen from his store 
and then get on with her life 
as far as im concerned they can let her go and she can go 
back and keep enjoying life pace said 
