more than 1 million britons are wheezing running 
fevers and nursing headaches during the nations worst outbreak of 
flu in 15 years doctors said thursday five flurelated deaths 
have been reported 
among those who are suffering from what doctors call the english 
flu is queen elizabeth ii this strain physicians say is a 
variant of the hong kong flu that swept britain in the winter of 
197475 
the royal society of general practitioners said thursday that 
infection levels have reached epidemic levels and it expects 
400000 more cases to develop in the next four weeks 
it said 109 people in every 100000 had influenza last week and 
a further 154 in every 100000 had influenzalike illness when the 
sickness rate tops 100 per 100000 the outbreak is considered an 
epidemic 
infection levels in 197475 rose to an average weekly rate of 
350 per 100000 people the society said 
the dead are a 16monthold child a 7yearold two elderly 
people and a 35yearold woman who was six months pregnant her 
baby could not be saved 
symptoms of the disease include fatigue aching muscles 
headaches coughing and prolonged fever lasting four or five days 
three million doses of flu vaccine have been administered and 
new stock has been flown in from france west germany and the 
netherlands 
