leung said while massachusetts and louisiana sit at the bottom 
of the rankings the two states have different situations in 
louisiana its more fundamental economic issues he said 
here its much different 
in massachusetts the growth in the deficit is related to a 
weakening economy but more importantly the lack of timely action 
to deal with it led us to lower the rating he said 
other states have had fiscal troubles but they have done a 
better job keeping their books balanced and maintaining their bond 
ratings 
there are many states with weaker economies than massachusetts 
that have higher bond ratings swerdling said 
