<TEXT>
dan aykroyd sits in a manhattan hotel room with 
a cigarette all fired up puffs of smoke quickly fill the air his 
face temporarily obscured 
even without the dark glasses he wears as elwood of the blues 
brothers fame aykroyd remains mysterious part biker part 
bookworm hes a private man who is gifted at imitating others 
richard nixon jimmy carter julia child but without the 
distinctive mannerisms that would tempt anyone to mimic dan aykroyd 
thats why hes always enjoyed surrounding himself with 
instantly recognizable stars such as bill murray in 
ghostbusters and eddie murphy in trading places an assist 
is as good as a goal aykroyd reasons using the appropriate sports 
metaphor for a native canadian on or offcamera he likes staying 
behind the scenes 
so he happily accepted the advice of a fellow biker who urged 
the actor to audition for the film driving miss daisy based on 
the play by alfred uhry 
billed third behind veterans morgan freeman and jessica tandy 
aykroyds jitters about playing a dramatic role were eased by the 
presence of his fellow actors and director bruce beresford 
tender mercies crimes of the heart 
when youre surrounded by such a great cast with the 
qualities they bring to a piece youre pretty well insulated 
said aykroyd 37 who portrays boolie the patient but 
longsuffering son of tandys eccentric southern jewish matron 
daisy werthan 
i really like to lay on a thick voice a thick persona a 
thick accent its just the kind of character work i enjoy doing i 
think its more interesting than going on screen and being ones 
self which is an awful lot of screen performance today 
as a screenwriter himself ghostbusters dragnet 
aykroyd admired the dimensions uhry gives to his character 
boolies drive for success and the material world the desire to be 
accepted by high society as an actor he enjoyed adding another 
look to his cast of 1000 faces 
it was a period piece so you got to wear a costume and got to 
drive an old car he said all of that helps in enriching the 
performance i like costumes and wigs and funny glasses and hats 
whenever you put me in costume it helps me a bit 
the way they tandy and freeman played the age makeup was 
really spectacular here they are in full full face makeup and 
yet the changes in physical motion and the voice were really subtle 
i was ready to be he says in a deep voice foghorn 
leghorn the rooster 
talking about comics who have tried serious roles such as robin 
williams and steve martin aykroyd said i think the only 
limitations are not in the peoples talents but in the perceptions 
of the audience 
if people are going to be dragged down at all its by the 
smirkers in the audience who want them to do something wild 
aykroyd born in ottawa in 1952 always loved to do imitations 
as a child copying the voices he heard on radio and television 
he was active in drama at the university of ottawa and in 1972 
joined chicagos acclaimed second city improvisational troupe 
meeting up with john belushi chevy chase gilda radner and others 
who three years later formed the original cast of televisions 
saturday night live 
were reminded about its impact on the television form all the 
time said aykroyd who along with belushi left the show in 1979 
to pursue a film career 
weve lost john and lost gilda so weve had much cause to 
reflect and think about the past through those two losses i follow 
the new show i watch it all the time i like to feel im part of 
it in a spiritual way 
aykroyd a longtime science fiction fan cares deeply about the 
spiritual world while murray concerned himself with earthly 
matters in ghostbusters gleefully pursuing sigourney weaver 
aykroyd and softspoken harold ramis discussed demons and slime 
with the enthusiasm of kids playing dungeons and dragons 
i love working with harold he said we got to do all the 
technical exposition which a lot of actors dont like doing but i 
enjoy it i like all that verbiage long passages of technical 
dialogue 
science fiction does change the way you look at the world 
ghostbusters was essentially science fiction harnessed for 
comedys purpose 
this dimension as aykroyd calls it lately has kept him 
busy his wife actress donna dixon recently gave birth to a 
daughter danielle alexandra professionally aykroyd promises 
tricks old and new 
i have a cable project with al franken and tom davis wed 
like to make some day he said we call it nixon in the navy 
its about his old navy days what hes done there in the pacific 
wed do it in five parts on a comedy channel or something 
</TEXT>
