stages in the development of skin cancer may be affected by uv 
exposure and may involve production of destructive oxygen species 
that can be counteracted by antioxidants 
our work should therefore suggest valuable and new approaches 
both to prevention of skin cancer and to protection against an 
adverse outcome once cancerous changes have begun 
