the restrictions on certain types of loans and socalled 
highrisk transactions such as funding leveraged buyouts 
parallel corporate adjustments underway at columbia to comply with 
recent legislation signed by president bush to end the nations 
thrift crisis 
in a nov 20 letter to columbia regulators said the thrifts 
