paying any new dividends to shareholders the thrift last paid a 
dividend on nov 28 at 7 cents a share 
columbia also needs to seek federal approval before funding any 
nonreal estate commercial loans and risky transactions including 
leveraged buyouts in which a company is bought and the debt paid 
off through cash from the sale of assets or operations 
the restrictions will remain in effect until regulators approve 
a new plan to be submitted by columbia on how it will meet the new 
federal capital guidelines 
